## Walkthrough

Implements standardized wizard navigation by introducing `wizardReturnView` state to track user return destinations when exiting the wizard, adding back buttons across wizard steps with consistent UI patterns, extracting About/Updates UI into a dedicated `AboutView` component, and refactoring `Options.tsx` to use the new component while updating hotkey navigation.

## Changes

|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|
|---|---|
|**Changeset & Documentation** <br> `.changeset/dull-regions-play.md`|Adds changeset documenting minor release for wizard navigation standardization, Options refactoring, and hover consistency improvements.|
|**State Management & App Context** <br> `src/hooks/useAppState.ts`, `src/components/AppContent.tsx`, `src/components/wizard/types.ts`|Introduces `wizardReturnView` state in hook; threads it through AppContent initialization, navigation handlers, and wizard invocations; adds optional `returnView` prop to WizardProps type.|
|**View Components** <br> `src/components/AboutView.tsx`, `src/components/Options.tsx`, `src/components/ForensicView.tsx`, `src/components/ManualFontGuide.tsx`|Creates new AboutView component (130 lines) for About/Updates panel; refactors Options to delegate about view to AboutView, updates hotkey navigation from escape/backspace to "b" key, reorganizes logs action layout; replaces inline Hotkey components with clickable bordered boxes in ForensicView and ManualFontGuide.|
|**Wizard Core Navigation** <br> `src/components/wizard/WizardContainer.tsx`, `src/components/wizard/WizardFooter.tsx`|Augments option sets with back entries across multiple steps, handles `opt.type === "back"` in confirmSelection and keyboard routing, adds `returnView` prop to signature (unused), updates footer text from "ESC to Exit" to "[B]ack to return".|

## Sequence Diagram(s)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant AppContent
    participant WizardContainer
    participant WizardStep
    
    User->>AppContent: Initiates wizard (s key or start action)
    AppContent->>AppContent: setWizardReturnView("dashboard")
    AppContent->>WizardContainer: setView("wizard")
    
    loop Wizard Navigation
        User->>WizardStep: Navigate through steps
        WizardStep->>WizardStep: Render back option in allOptions
        User->>WizardStep: Click back button
        WizardStep->>WizardContainer: back() called
    end
    
    WizardContainer->>WizardContainer: confirmSelection({type: "back"})
    WizardContainer->>AppContent: onCancel ‚Üí uses wizardReturnView
    AppContent->>AppContent: setView(wizardReturnView)
    AppContent->>User: Returns to recorded destination
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Options
    participant AboutView
    participant AppContent
    
    User->>Options: Opens Options menu
    Options->>AboutView: Render AboutView component
    AboutView->>AboutView: Display version, update status
    User->>AboutView: Interact with update check/control
    AboutView->>AboutView: handleUpdate(), setUpdateStatus()
    User->>AboutView: Click back (b key)
    AboutView->>Options: setSubView("menu")
    Options->>User: Return to options menu
```

## Estimated code review effort

üéØ 4 (Complex) | ‚è±Ô∏è ~60 minutes

The changes involve significant state threading across multiple components, a new pattern for wizard navigation consistency applied across 30+ files, heterogeneous refactoring in Options.tsx with behavioral changes, and complex option augmentation logic in WizardContainer. While many changes follow a repetitive back-button pattern (reducing individual file review effort), the diversity of wizard step implementations, state management updates, and the coordinated navigation flow across AppContent ‚Üí WizardContainer ‚Üí individual steps requires careful analysis of integration points and state consistency.
